<NOTE PLACE="foot"><HI>v.</HI> 16. Quomodo <HI>Abraham</HI> Emeril &agrave; filiis <HI>Emor</HI> monumentum? Cum hoede <HI>Jacobo</HI> dicatur, <HI>Gen.</HI> 33.19. &amp; <HI>Jo&s;h.</HI> 24.32. <HI>Ma&s;ius</HI> multique alii textum putant &agrave; librariis corruptum, &amp; nomen <HI>Abrahami</HI> irrep&s;i&s;&s;e, additum &agrave; quodam &s;ciolo de&s;criptore, cum nomen <HI>Jacobi</HI> &agrave; prioribus repetitum rect&egrave; conveniat cum verbo <HI>emerit.</HI> Ludovicus Capellus vult loco <HI>Abraham</HI> legendum <GAP LANG="grc" DESC="foreign" RESP="OXF">, nepos &s;cilicet <HI>Abrahami Jacobus. Rivetus</HI> facit nomen Patronymicum <HI>Abraham</HI> pro <HI>Abrahamides</HI> &amp; huju&s;modi phra&s;eos varia <HI>Salmeron</HI> &amp; <HI>A Lapide</HI> exempla afferunt, t&ugrave;m ex &s;acris t&ugrave;m ex profanis literis. Vide plura in <HI>Rob. Bailii</HI> opere Hi&s;t. &amp; Chronolog. Sunt qui <HI>Abrahamum</HI> putant ideo pro Jacobo nominari, quia Parentes, &amp; filii idem e&s;&s;e <HI>moralit&egrave;r</HI> cen&s;entur, atque i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">de e&s;&s;e quod 1 <HI>Reg.</HI> 12.16. Populus <HI>Roboamo</HI> in&s;en&s;us, dicit, <HI>quae pars nobis in Davide? i. e.</HI> in <HI>Roboamo Davidis</HI> nepote, &amp; quod 1 <HI>Reg.</HI> 15.6. Perpetuum bellum in|terce&s;&s;i&s;&s;e legitur inter <HI>Roboamum,</HI> &amp; <HI>Jeroboamum</HI> quamdiu hic &s;uit in vivis. Ubi <HI>Roboami</HI> nomine, qui pridem obierat, <HI>Abias</HI> filius intelligitur, qui gravit&egrave;r afflixit I&s;raelitas u&s;que ad obitum <HI>Jeroboami.</HI> 2 <HI>Paral.</HI> 13.17, 18, 19, 20. Sic Chri&s;to tribuitur <HI>Davidis</HI> nomen, <HI>Jer.</HI> 30.9. &amp; <HI>Ezek.</HI> 34.23. <HI>Bochartus pag.</HI> 435. <GAP LANG="grc" DESC="foreign" RESP="OXF"> verti &s;olet quod emerat <HI>Abrahamus</HI> cum ex &s;acr&acirc; hi&s;tori&acirc; con&s;tat non <HI>Abrahamum,</HI> &s;ed <HI>Jaco|bum</HI> eum agrum emi&s;&s;e. At cum articulus non exprimatur tam dativus &s;ubintelligi pote&s;t, quam nominativus, ut &s;en&s;us &s;it <GAP LANG="grc" DESC="foreign" RESP="OXF">, quod emerat (&s;cili|cet <HI>Jacob</HI> de quo commate praecedente) <HI>Abrahamo.</HI> Et&s;i enim <HI>Abrahamus</HI> diem &s;uum jam obii&s;&s;et, ip&s;i tamen dici pote&s;t emptus i&s;te ager, ad de&s;ignandum &s;copum, quem in agri emptione habuit <HI>Jacob,</HI> qui non &s;uit duntaxat, ut eo pro &s;epulchreto uteretur (neminem enim i&s;tie <HI>Jacobus</HI> in humavit, nec ip&s;e ibi inhumatus e&s;t, &s;ed in &s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">e|lune&aacute; Maepelae, <HI>Gen.</HI> 49.30. &amp; 23.16.) &s;ed vel maxim&egrave;, ut primitiae quaedam e&s;&s;ent terrae Canaan cujus totius Haereditatem <HI>Abrahamo</HI> Deus, &amp; &s;emini ejus promi&s;erat, quippe cui prim&ograve; <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">acta e&s;t promi&s;&s;io, ut haeres mundi e&s;&s;et, <HI>Rom.</HI> 4.13. Atque ibi &s;imul cau&s;a latet cur non tantum Jo&s;ephus &s;ed (quod hic &agrave; St. Stephano di&s;cimus) reliqui etiam Patriarchae &agrave; Po&s;teris haereditatem terrae promi&s;&s;ae jam capientibus, Sichemum &s;int tran&s;lati, atque in ejus agro &s;epulti, nempe quia ager i&s;te emptus erat <HI>Abrahamo</HI> tanquam pignus haereditatis totius terrae, <HI>Abrahamo</HI> promi&s;&s;ae. <HI>De Dicu. Gen.</HI> 33.19. <HI>Jacob</HI> emi&s;&s;e legitur partem agri &s;iliorum <HI>Hemor</HI> <GAP LANG="grc" DESC="foreign" RESP="OXF"> centum agnis. Forta&s;&s;e pro ag<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">is, <HI>nummi</HI> intelligendi &s;unt <HI>agni</HI> effigie &s;ignati, quales cudi&s;&s;e legitur Servius Rex Romanorum: Forta&s;&s;&egrave; argenti vel pecuniae nomine eo loco cen&s;eri po&s;&s;it quicquid ill&acirc; ae|tate prae&s;tabat pecuniae vices. <HI>Bochart. lib.</HI> 1. <HI>cap.</HI> 2. <HI>de ammalib.</HI></NOTE>
