<P><HI>v.</HI> 9. And they that w<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">re with the law indeed the light, and were afraid; but they he<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">rd not th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter"> voice of him that &s;pak<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter"> to me.</P>
<P><HI>v.</HI> 10. And I &s;aid, Wh<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">t &s;hall I do, Lord? And the Lord &s;aid unto me, Ari&s;e, and g<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter"> into D<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="3 letters">&s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">us, and there it &s;hall be told thee of all things which are appointed for th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="2 letters"> to do.</P>
