<P><HI>v.</HI> 13. At mid-day, O king, I &s;aw in the way a light from heaven, above the brightne&s;s of the &s;un, &s;hining round about me, and them which journeyed with me.</P>
<P><HI>v.</HI> 14. And when we were all fallen to the earth, I heard a voice &s;peaking unto me, and &s;aying in the Hebrew tongue, Saul, S<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">ul, why per&s;ecute&s;t thou me? It is hard for thee to kick again&s;t the pricks.</P>
