<P><HI>v.</HI> 16. But ari&s;e, and &s;tand up upon thy feet, for I have appeared unto thee for this purpo&s;e, to make thee a mini&s;ter and a witn<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">&s;s, both of the&s;e things which thou ha&s;t &s;een, and of tho&s;e things in the which I will appear unto thee.</P>
<PB N="53" REF="36">
<P><HI>v.</HI> 17. Delivering thee from the people, and from the Gentiles, unto whom I now &s;end thee,</P>
<P><HI>v.</HI> 18. To open their eyes, and to turn them from darkne&s;s to light, and from the power of Satan unto God, that they may receive forgivene&s;s of &s;ins, and inheritance among them which are &s;anctified by faith that is in me.</P></Q>
