the &s;p<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">ce of <HI>Nine months;</HI> which with the <HI>Two years</HI> he taught in the <HI>School of Tyrannus,</HI> and the <HI>Three months</HI> he taught in the <HI>J<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">wi&s;h Synago<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">ues</HI> a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter"> <HI>Eph<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">&s;us,</HI> will m<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">ke up the &s;pace of <HI>Three years&punc;</HI> that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">e &s;a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">s, he laboured in <HI>A&s;ia [Act.</HI> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="2 letters">.31.]: <HI>A gr<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">at Door b<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">ing op<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">ned to him in that place, though there were many adver&s;aries,</HI> 1 Cor. 16.9.</P>
